OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHouse of Commons to be     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'menopause friendly',      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FSpeaker Lindsay Hoyle vows 
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle has signed a 
OL,6, pledge vowing to make the House of     
OL,7, Commons "menopause friendly" for staff.
OL,9,FThe pledge commits employers to        
OL,10,Fsupporting employees affected by the   
OL,11,Fmenopause, for example by providing    
OL,12,Faccess to fans or flexible working.    
OL,14,FSir Lindsay said women ran his office  
OL,15,Fand he didn't want to see them leave   
OL,16,Fbecause of the menopause.              
OL,18,FThe Commons Speaker said it should not 
OL,19,Fbe a "taboo subject" that was "swept   
OL,20,Funder the carpet".                     
